Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the National Museum for Women in the Arts in Washington, D.C. He expressed gratitude for the support and recognition he and his wife, Karen Pence, have received. Pence highlighted the accomplishments of the state of Indiana, including tax reforms, military rebuilding, and deregulation. He also praised the Hoosiers who have played a leading role in supporting President Trump's administration. Pence acknowledged various Indiana politicians and officials who have contributed to the country's success, including members of Congress and members of his Cabinet. He also mentioned the achievements of Hoosiers in fields like space exploration and national security. Pence expressed his pride in his wife's work, particularly in promoting art therapy and supporting military families. He concluded by thanking the audience for their kindness and support, and expressed his commitment to continue working hard to make them proud.